1
00:00:09,933 --> 00:00:14,233
<i>There was a time
when my mom, my brother, and I</i>

2
00:00:14,367 --> 00:00:15,400
<i> had to sleep on the street.</i>

3
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:17,500
<i> We have a demolition order!</i>

4
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:21,800
<i>I promised that I would
give them a better life,</i>

5
00:00:21,933 --> 00:00:23,167
<i> a house we can call our own.</i>

6
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,400
<i> Marj, congrats!</i>

7
00:00:24,533 --> 00:00:27,200
<i>You stole the clients
I worked hard to get.</i>

8
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:29,833
<i>Thea, I didn't need to steal
your clients to get ahead.</i>

9
00:00:29,967 --> 00:00:33,033
<i> Well, I'm this man's wife!</i>

10
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:34,267
<i> You turned me into a mistress!</i>

11
00:00:34,433 --> 00:00:36,667
<i>It will affect the image
of our company.</i>

12
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:39,300
<i>That's why I decided
to let the two of you go.</i>

13
00:00:39,433 --> 00:00:40,733
<i> Why don't you try applying</i>

14
00:00:40,867 --> 00:00:42,200
<i>to the company
I'm transferring to?</i>

15
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:43,633
<i> At Torrecampo Realty.</i>

16
00:00:43,767 --> 00:00:45,767
<i>- Am I late?
- You'll be fine.</i>

17
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:48,000
<i>Everyone's willing to wait
for the golden boy.</i>

18
00:00:48,133 --> 00:00:49,833
<i>You'd better watch your mouth,
Edward.</i>

19
00:00:49,967 --> 00:00:51,433
<i> Don't embarrass our family.</i>

20
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:54,833
<i>Mr. Valderama is looking for
a new house for his daughter.</i>

21
00:00:54,967 --> 00:00:56,733
<i> There's something else I want.</i>

22
00:00:56,867 --> 00:00:58,633
<i>Excuse me, I need to get
something upstairs.</i>

23
00:00:58,767 --> 00:00:59,433
<i> Pervert!</i>

24
00:00:59,567 --> 00:01:00,567
<i> You no longer work here!</i>

25
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:03,433
<i>Why did you follow us
here in our own home?</i>

26
00:01:03,567 --> 00:01:05,667
<i>My brother
is in a critical condition.</i>

27
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:09,333
<i>I'm begging you to help me,
please.</i>

28
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:10,533
<i> Please leave, Miss Castillo.</i>

29
00:01:10,667 --> 00:01:11,700
<i>You can go ahead
with the surgery.</i>

30
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:12,933
<i>I will take care of everything.</i>

31
00:01:13,067 --> 00:01:14,833
<i>Once he's fully recovered,
you can go back to work.</i>

32
00:01:14,967 --> 00:01:16,300
<i> Thank you so much.</i>

33
00:01:16,433 --> 00:01:20,000
<i>I will never forget
what you did to help us.</i>

34
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:23,333
Sir, this guy is throwing a fit
earlier.

35
00:01:23,467 --> 00:01:25,733
I understand, but you shouldn't
abuse your authority.

36
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:27,867
Have more patience.

37
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,700
I don't want this
to happen again.

38
00:01:29,833 --> 00:01:31,467
Okay, Sir. I'm sorry.

39
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:33,467
You don't need to apologize
to me. Apologize to them.

40
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:36,333
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

41
00:01:36,467 --> 00:01:38,267
- I'm so sorry.
- Go on.

42
00:01:41,567 --> 00:01:42,800
Are you okay?

43
00:01:42,933 --> 00:01:44,633
Sir Paolo.

44
00:01:44,767 --> 00:01:47,433
Thank you so much, Sir.

45
00:01:48,767 --> 00:01:51,400
You're a good guy.

46
00:01:51,533 --> 00:01:54,400
A good guy.

47
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:56,833
Thank you, you're kind Sir.

48
00:01:58,567 --> 00:02:00,367
Thank you.

49
00:02:54,133 --> 00:02:56,000
Jobert!

50
00:02:56,133 --> 00:02:57,467
Sis!

51
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:03,500
Mom, why didn't you tell me
that you're coming here?

52
00:03:03,633 --> 00:03:05,833
You didn't receive
my text message?

53
00:03:07,233 --> 00:03:10,233
My phone died.

54
00:03:10,367 --> 00:03:12,133
Are you okay?
Did the guard hurt you?

55
00:03:12,267 --> 00:03:13,300
It's okay, they're safe now.

56
00:03:13,433 --> 00:03:15,133
I have already
handled everything.

57
00:03:15,267 --> 00:03:17,167
They have nothing
on these muscles.

58
00:03:19,633 --> 00:03:20,633
I was almost impressed.

59
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,633
A hero, but an arrogant one.

60
00:03:23,767 --> 00:03:25,167
Did you say something?

61
00:03:28,633 --> 00:03:29,667
Oh, nothing.

62
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,967
I was just saying,

63
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:34,967
you're starting to make a habit
of saving my family.

64
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:37,667
Aside from the money I owe you,

65
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,400
I feel like I'll be forever
indebted to you.

66
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:42,933
You know, next time,

67
00:03:43,067 --> 00:03:45,500
let the guards know ahead of
time that you're expecting them

68
00:03:45,633 --> 00:03:48,567
so they can get in
without a problem.

69
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:50,967
Being your knight in shining
armor can get tiring too.

70
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:56,167
- Thanks again,
- Sir. You're welcome.

71
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:57,967
I'm going to get going now,
Mrs. Evelyn.

72
00:03:58,100 --> 00:04:00,133
Thanks again, Sir Paolo.

73
00:04:00,267 --> 00:04:03,367
Jobert, I'm going to go, okay?
Big bro will go now.

74
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,100
- Bye, Paolo.
- Okay, bye.

75
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:23,200
Girl, I'm going to go, okay?

76
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:25,133
Auntie, sit down, come on.

77
00:04:25,267 --> 00:04:26,633
Thank you.

78
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:28,300
Timmy, come with me.

79
00:04:28,467 --> 00:04:30,300
We have a lot of papers
to submit, come on.

80
00:04:32,133 --> 00:04:33,833
Wow, that's a big turtle.

81
00:04:33,967 --> 00:04:35,667
Marj,

82
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:39,967
if I had known that we would run
into Sir Paolo earlier,

83
00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:43,733
I would've made
some rice cakes for him.

84
00:04:43,867 --> 00:04:46,333
I could've given it to him
as a way of saying thanks

85
00:04:46,467 --> 00:04:49,967
for helping us
with Jobert's operation.

86
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:52,333
Oh, Mom, it's not like
he's going to eat rice cakes.

87
00:04:52,467 --> 00:04:53,333
He's a rich kid.

88
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:55,433
You never know.

89
00:04:55,567 --> 00:04:57,900
And wait a minute.

90
00:04:58,033 --> 00:05:01,400
I noticed something
about your boss.

91
00:05:01,567 --> 00:05:02,467
Yeah.

92
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:05,367
Why does your boss
seem so nice to you?

93
00:05:06,733 --> 00:05:08,900
Could it be that
he likes you?

94
00:05:09,033 --> 00:05:10,333
What?

95
00:05:11,533 --> 00:05:14,367
He likes my sister?

96
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,433
Hey, what are you talking about,
Jobert?

97
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:19,133
Here, watch the turtle.

98
00:05:19,267 --> 00:05:20,767
Come on, Mom.

99
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:23,933
Don't pay attention to
what she's saying, okay?

100
00:05:24,067 --> 00:05:28,167
Mom, don't make a big deal
out of Sir Paolo's help.

101
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:31,433
And don't give Jobert
any ideas, okay?

102
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:35,133
All right, go ahead
and sit there, Mom.

103
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:38,400
I just need to submit a few
files. I'll be right back.

104
00:05:38,533 --> 00:05:39,867
And then we'll go home, okay?

105
00:05:52,233 --> 00:05:54,033
Excuse me, Ma'am.

106
00:05:54,167 --> 00:05:55,200
Good afternoon.

107
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:56,300
Good afternoon.

108
00:05:56,433 --> 00:05:59,100
Are you Marj's family?

109
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:01,200
That's right.

110
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:05,200
I'm Edward,
I'm your daughter's friend.

111
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:07,067
Oh, so you're Edward.

112
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:10,433
Marj told me about you.

113
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,500
Really?

114
00:06:11,633 --> 00:06:12,700
Yes.

115
00:06:13,733 --> 00:06:16,967
Actually, your daughter
always talks about you, too.

116
00:06:18,467 --> 00:06:19,733
And that's Jobert?

117
00:06:19,867 --> 00:06:20,933
Yes.

118
00:06:21,067 --> 00:06:22,800
Jobert?

119
00:06:22,933 --> 00:06:25,633
Jobert, what are you watching?

120
00:06:25,767 --> 00:06:27,000
Turtle.

121
00:06:27,133 --> 00:06:30,933
Did you know that turtles
have a long life?

122
00:06:31,067 --> 00:06:33,567
They can live up to 50 years.

123
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:37,733
Wow, big bro Edward
didn't know that.

124
00:06:37,867 --> 00:06:38,867
Big bro?

125
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,900
Like my kind big bro?

126
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:42,433
Kind big bro?

127
00:06:42,567 --> 00:06:44,400
Who is that?

128
00:06:45,767 --> 00:06:48,900
Oh, that's what he
calls Sir Paolo.

129
00:06:50,033 --> 00:06:55,033
He likes Sir Paolo because
your brother helped us.

130
00:06:56,067 --> 00:06:58,333
He likes my big sister.

131
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,333
Jobert, that's enough, sweetie.

132
00:07:01,467 --> 00:07:02,900
Don't talk like that.

133
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:04,300
I'm sorry about that, Sir.

134
00:07:04,433 --> 00:07:06,233
He doesn't know
what he's talking about.

135
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:07,333
It's okay.

136
00:07:08,733 --> 00:07:10,467
Jobert,

137
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,300
just watch TV, sweetie.

138
00:07:12,433 --> 00:07:15,733
Look, look how big
that turtle is.

139
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,200
Is everything all right,
sweetie?

140
00:08:11,767 --> 00:08:12,933
Yeah.

141
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,700
I just remembered...

142
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:17,233
When I was a kid,

143
00:08:18,267 --> 00:08:21,333
I would stay up late
every night studying.

144
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:26,333
And I joined every sport
there was,

145
00:08:26,467 --> 00:08:29,300
because I wanted to at least win
some kind of award.

146
00:08:29,433 --> 00:08:31,433
To be displayed here.

147
00:08:31,567 --> 00:08:33,433
Just one, I'm happy with that.

148
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:38,633
Sweetie, awards
are not important at all.

149
00:08:38,767 --> 00:08:41,400
That's not the measure
of your worth.

150
00:08:41,533 --> 00:08:46,500
And you shouldn't be competing
with your brother.

151
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:47,533
I have to.

152
00:08:49,033 --> 00:08:52,667
Because that's the only way
I can earn my place.

153
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:56,133
So you would notice me, too.

154
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:01,233
Why is it like that, Mom?

155
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:05,033
With Paolo, it seems like...

156
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:10,067
winning comes so easily to him.

157
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,500
And...

158
00:09:13,033 --> 00:09:15,000
he gets whatever he wants.

159
00:09:15,133 --> 00:09:16,467
Wait a minute.

160
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:21,000
Did you and your sibling
have an argument again?

161
00:09:21,133 --> 00:09:22,100
No.

162
00:09:22,233 --> 00:09:23,467
Not really, Mom.

163
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:26,667
I'm just tired
of always being the loser.

164
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:31,800
I'm so tired of losing
and not getting what I want.

165
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:36,400
Right now, Mom.

166
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:38,633
There's this girl that...

167
00:09:38,767 --> 00:09:40,067
I really like.

168
00:09:42,767 --> 00:09:44,567
And...

169
00:09:44,700 --> 00:09:46,933
I will do everything to win her.

170
00:09:47,067 --> 00:09:48,800
Because I don't want
to lose her.

171
00:09:48,933 --> 00:09:50,233
Okay.

172
00:09:52,533 --> 00:09:54,367
Oh my goodness, sweetie.

173
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:03,700
Sir, Miss Castillo's here.

174
00:10:10,033 --> 00:10:11,300
Sit down.

175
00:10:19,233 --> 00:10:21,033
You called me here.

176
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:26,667
Do you need something, Sir?

177
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:30,600
I just want to discuss
the incident with Mr. Valderama.

178
00:10:30,733 --> 00:10:32,433
I understand

179
00:10:32,567 --> 00:10:35,567
that you felt offended
about what happened.

180
00:10:35,733 --> 00:10:38,400
But I've known Harry
for a long time.

181
00:10:38,533 --> 00:10:42,800
He's a devoted husband and a
loving father to two daughters.

182
00:10:46,367 --> 00:10:48,633
What did I have to do with them?

183
00:10:50,967 --> 00:10:53,167
What I mean to say is...

184
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:55,533
What happened could have
been just an accident.

185
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:59,533
Perhaps Harry just
accidentally brushed...

186
00:11:02,233 --> 00:11:03,467
onto your buttocks.

187
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:07,067
He will not risk his name
and reputation

188
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:09,033
by doing such things.

189
00:11:10,167 --> 00:11:11,900
You must have just overreacted.

190
00:11:14,133 --> 00:11:14,900
But Sir...

191
00:11:15,033 --> 00:11:17,200
You could have been...

192
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:19,933
stressed or exhausted
when that happened.

193
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:24,033
And you have misinterpreted
the client's intention.

194
00:11:26,233 --> 00:11:27,433
Listen,

195
00:11:27,567 --> 00:11:30,967
I don't want this to go
any further, Miss Castillo.

196
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:35,767
I want to retain Mr. Valderama
as our valued client.

197
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:39,467
That's why I want you to go to
him and apologize in person.

198
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:47,500
You're not going to decline
my request, right?

199
00:11:48,567 --> 00:11:50,200
After all,

200
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:52,067
you're indebted to us,

201
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:57,933
since my son helped you save
your brother.

202
00:11:58,067 --> 00:11:59,600
Remember?

203
00:12:04,667 --> 00:12:07,333
I will go to him to apologize.

204
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:14,000
Good.

205
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:17,167
I didn't come here
to argue with you.

206
00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:19,867
I came here to apologize.

207
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:22,767
I've hurt and accused you.

208
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:25,067
I hope you can forgive me.

209
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,100
And that it won't affect
your business deals

210
00:12:27,233 --> 00:12:29,033
with Torrecampo Realty.

211
00:12:32,467 --> 00:12:35,300
I also want to apologize to you,
Miss Castillo.

212
00:12:35,433 --> 00:12:38,467
You almost lost your job
because of that incident.

213
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:40,867
You don't need to worry
about that anymore, Sir.

214
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:43,400
I'm back at work now.

215
00:12:43,533 --> 00:12:46,533
The important thing is,
we got this straightened out.

216
00:12:46,667 --> 00:12:49,467
Well, I'm glad
we can put that behind us now.

217
00:12:50,633 --> 00:12:53,733
Well, we should celebrate
this moment.

218
00:12:53,867 --> 00:12:55,400
No, thank you.

219
00:13:09,167 --> 00:13:12,000
Sir, they might look for me
at the office.

220
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:14,667
Thank you,
but I'm going to have to pass.

221
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:17,533
It's just one drink.
You won't get drunk.

222
00:13:19,533 --> 00:13:21,400
Come on, Miss Castillo.

223
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:23,400
Please grant my request.

224
00:13:30,767 --> 00:13:32,133
Cheers?

225
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:37,333
Cheers.

226
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:54,000
Good morning, Gemma.

227
00:13:54,133 --> 00:13:55,667
Could you please get me
a cup of coffee

228
00:13:55,833 --> 00:13:57,900
and cancel all my appointments
for today?

229
00:13:58,033 --> 00:13:59,367
I had a bad hangover.

230
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,767
Okay, Sir.

231
00:14:02,433 --> 00:14:03,767
And...

232
00:14:04,867 --> 00:14:07,333
can you call Miss Tough Girl?

233
00:14:07,467 --> 00:14:10,467
I mean, Miss Castillo
from her cubicle.

234
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,833
Sir, as far as I know,

235
00:14:11,967 --> 00:14:13,267
Marj is out of the office
right now.

236
00:14:15,233 --> 00:14:17,067
We don't have
an open house today.

237
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:20,267
Your dad asked her
to go see Mr. Valderama.

238
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:29,467
Sir, what's the matter?

239
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:38,233
Thank you, Sir,
but I have to get going.

240
00:14:38,367 --> 00:14:40,333
Are you sure you
don't want to stay?

241
00:14:40,467 --> 00:14:42,633
So we can talk more.

242
00:14:42,767 --> 00:14:43,733
Thank you for your time.

243
00:14:43,867 --> 00:14:46,833
But they need me
at the office.

244
00:14:46,967 --> 00:14:48,333
Are you sure?

245
00:14:50,367 --> 00:14:52,167
Are you all right,
Miss Castillo?

246
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:56,267
I just felt a little dizzy,
but I'm okay.

247
00:15:19,233 --> 00:15:20,567
Please, don't.

248
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,967
Sir, please, no.

249
00:15:35,233 --> 00:15:37,267
Good afternoon, Mr. Torrecampo.

250
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:38,800
Mr. Valderama!

251
00:15:41,267 --> 00:15:43,067
Get off of her!

252
00:15:45,067 --> 00:15:47,500
There are so many bars out
there if you want a good time.

253
00:15:47,633 --> 00:15:49,300
If you want,
I can accompany you.

254
00:15:49,433 --> 00:15:50,667
Stay out of this, Paolo!

255
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:51,733
I can't!

256
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:53,533
You drugged my employee!

257
00:15:53,667 --> 00:15:56,467
If you want,
let's just take this outside.

258
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:59,633
If you want me
to break every bone you have.

259
00:15:59,767 --> 00:16:02,000
You're insane!

260
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:08,467
You bastard!

261
00:16:08,633 --> 00:16:11,667
I will pull out all of my
investments in your company!

262
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,900
Don't threaten me!

263
00:16:14,033 --> 00:16:15,833
Because I can file a case
of attempted rape

264
00:16:15,967 --> 00:16:18,233
and acts of lasciviousness
against you!

265
00:16:18,367 --> 00:16:20,333
And I have a witness!

266
00:16:20,467 --> 00:16:22,300
So don't even try me!

267
00:16:41,867 --> 00:16:44,000
Sir? Sir Paolo.

268
00:16:44,133 --> 00:16:47,300
Don't worry, you're safe now.

269
00:16:58,267 --> 00:17:00,300
<i>- How is your brother now?
- He's okay now.</i>

270
00:17:00,433 --> 00:17:03,200
<i>-I'm glad Sir Paolo helped me.
- Who's that kind big bro?</i>

271
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:06,633
<i>That's what he calls Sir Paolo.</i>

272
00:17:06,767 --> 00:17:08,933
<i> He likes my big sister.</i>

273
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,300
Sir!

274
00:17:13,433 --> 00:17:15,567
It's Marj, Sir!
Something happened to her!

275
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:18,233
What happened?

276
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:21,800
Thankfully, she only ingested
a small amount

277
00:17:21,933 --> 00:17:24,133
of depressant drugs.

278
00:17:24,267 --> 00:17:25,933
All her vitals are normal.

279
00:17:26,067 --> 00:17:27,933
So there's no need
to confine her.

280
00:17:30,133 --> 00:17:31,833
- Thank you.
- Excuse me.

281
00:17:42,933 --> 00:17:45,133
Sir, thank you,
that you came.

282
00:17:45,267 --> 00:17:47,933
If you weren't there,something
bad might happen to me.

283
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,933
Mr. Valderama got nothing on me.

284
00:17:52,067 --> 00:17:55,833
And I had a bad hangover.

285
00:17:55,967 --> 00:17:58,867
Sir, thank you so much.

286
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,267
I was so scared.

287
00:18:03,067 --> 00:18:06,833
My mom, my brother.

288
00:18:06,967 --> 00:18:09,300
They're the only ones
I think about.

289
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:12,100
I'm the only one
they can count on.

290
00:18:12,233 --> 00:18:14,867
What if something
bad happened to me?

291
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:19,000
I don't know what I'll do.
I couldn't bear it.

292
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:23,500
Don't cry, don't cry.

293
00:18:23,633 --> 00:18:25,533
Don't cry, stop crying.

294
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:27,900
Aren't you Miss Tough Girl?

295
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:52,100
Nurse, excuse me.

296
00:18:52,233 --> 00:18:55,600
Where is Miss
Marjorie Castillo?

297
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:57,633
Marjorie Castillo?

298
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:04,033
That way, Sir.

299
00:19:20,567 --> 00:19:23,167
Sorry, sorry,
I'm sorry, Sir.

300
00:19:26,467 --> 00:19:27,733
Sorry for what?

301
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:30,833
I hugged you.

302
00:19:30,967 --> 00:19:32,300
I'm sorry.

303
00:19:32,433 --> 00:19:34,733
I just got carried away.

304
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:39,333
I know I always have
that affect on you.

305
00:19:48,567 --> 00:19:51,167
Thank you, Sir Paolo.

306
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:52,700
Thank you, Sir.

307
00:19:53,733 --> 00:19:55,333
You're welcome.

308
00:20:05,133 --> 00:20:06,500
Okay, Ma'am.

309
00:20:12,233 --> 00:20:13,867
We're good to go.

310
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,133
Let me give you a lift.

311
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:17,433
Thank you, Sir Paolo.

312
00:20:17,567 --> 00:20:19,233
But you don't need
to give me a lift,

313
00:20:19,367 --> 00:20:21,033
I can take care of myself now.

314
00:20:21,167 --> 00:20:23,267
Just call me Paolo.

315
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,667
And...

316
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:26,133
it's the least
I could do for you.

317
00:20:26,267 --> 00:20:27,600
After everything happened.

318
00:20:28,700 --> 00:20:31,667
I'm still a gentleman.

319
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:34,167
My mom might see you, Sir.

320
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:36,900
Paolo.

321
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:40,867
I'm sure she'll
wonder what happened.

322
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:43,167
She'll ask questions,

323
00:20:43,300 --> 00:20:45,967
and I don't want them
to find out about this.

324
00:20:46,100 --> 00:20:48,933
I don't want them
to worry about me.

325
00:20:49,067 --> 00:20:50,467
Fair enough.

326
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:52,700
Okay, just...

327
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:55,367
don't forget what the doctor
said, all right?

328
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:58,233
The drug they gave you
will still affect your body

329
00:20:58,367 --> 00:21:00,967
for the next 6 to 12 hours.

330
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:03,300
So you still need to rest.

331
00:21:05,167 --> 00:21:07,833
Until it completely wears off.

332
00:21:09,633 --> 00:21:13,233
And when you're ready,
let me know, okay?

333
00:21:13,367 --> 00:21:16,500
I'll go with you to file a
complaint against Mr. Valderama.

334
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:18,700
No, please.

335
00:21:18,833 --> 00:21:20,967
I don't want to add
to your problems

336
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:23,267
or your expenses because of me.

337
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,233
You already have so
much on your plate.

338
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:26,600
And besides,

339
00:21:26,733 --> 00:21:29,400
he's a powerful man, the kind
you don't just go up against.

340
00:21:32,167 --> 00:21:33,533
Okay.

341
00:21:35,733 --> 00:21:37,400
It's up to you.

342
00:21:37,533 --> 00:21:40,100
But remember this, okay?

343
00:21:40,233 --> 00:21:42,100
I always got your back.

344
00:21:42,267 --> 00:21:43,967
And I will make sure

345
00:21:44,100 --> 00:21:47,833
that we won't be making business
deals with him anymore.

346
00:21:47,967 --> 00:21:49,267
You can trust me on that.

347
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,433
Thank you, Paolo.

348
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:54,333
You're welcome.

349
00:21:54,467 --> 00:21:57,133
Stop crying. You're Miss Tough
Girl, remember?

350
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:12,767
Hi, Jobert.

351
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:15,033
Marj, why do you look like that?

352
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:17,367
Did something happen, sweetie?

353
00:22:17,500 --> 00:22:20,967
Nothing, Mom.
I'm just exhausted.

354
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:23,667
Come, sit down, it's
time for dinner.

355
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:26,200
I'm going to set the table,
okay?

356
00:22:51,733 --> 00:22:53,500
I got that, Mom.

357
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:04,567
Jobert, what
are you doing?

358
00:23:04,700 --> 00:23:07,933
Big sissy's not okay.

359
00:23:08,067 --> 00:23:09,900
You look scared.

360
00:23:11,233 --> 00:23:14,000
I'm just worried.

361
00:23:14,133 --> 00:23:19,067
I'm thinking if you're
behaving while I'm at work?

362
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:29,767
Jobert's a good boy, right?

363
00:23:29,900 --> 00:23:33,200
Sis,

364
00:23:33,333 --> 00:23:37,000
if they're being mean to you,

365
00:23:37,133 --> 00:23:39,467
you tell Jobert, okay?

366
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:46,300
I will fight for you.

367
00:23:46,433 --> 00:23:48,300
I will defend you.

368
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:53,400
I will.

369
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:59,100
They'll get scared if they
find out you'll fight for me.

370
00:24:10,633 --> 00:24:12,100
Hi, Weng.

371
00:24:17,533 --> 00:24:18,967
Hey, what's with
the serious face?

372
00:24:22,100 --> 00:24:23,800
I saw you.

373
00:24:23,933 --> 00:24:24,900
What?

374
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:28,433
I saw you and Marj at the ER.

375
00:24:29,867 --> 00:24:31,233
What was that about?

376
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:33,700
Oh, come on.

377
00:24:33,833 --> 00:24:36,967
It's not like you haven't
seen me with other girls before.

378
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:38,267
What's the big deal?

379
00:24:45,033 --> 00:24:46,067
What happened to her?

380
00:24:48,433 --> 00:24:51,333
Mr. Valderama tried
to take advantage of her.

381
00:24:51,467 --> 00:24:52,800
But don't worry, she's safe now.

382
00:24:52,933 --> 00:24:54,700
I handled everything already.

383
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,867
Are we good?
Did I answer all your questions?

384
00:25:00,233 --> 00:25:01,967
Do you like her?

385
00:25:09,900 --> 00:25:11,300
Wait.

386
00:25:11,433 --> 00:25:14,867
Are you acting like this
because you like her?

387
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:16,367
Do you like her?

388
00:25:17,500 --> 00:25:19,333
What if I tell you
that I like her?

389
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:22,933
I like Marj.

390
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:25,900
I really like her a lot.

391
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,333
What about you?

392
00:25:30,467 --> 00:25:32,133
Do you like her, too?

393
00:25:47,067 --> 00:25:49,767
Mom, who's that?

394
00:25:49,900 --> 00:25:52,100
It's nothing. Nobody.

395
00:25:52,233 --> 00:25:54,267
- Who's that?
- It's nothing, Marj.

396
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:56,533
- Here, I got it.
- Marj, I got it.

397
00:25:56,667 --> 00:25:58,700
Marj.

398
00:25:58,833 --> 00:26:01,300
Why are you hiding your phone?
Who is it?

399
00:26:01,433 --> 00:26:02,500
Mom!

400
00:26:07,267 --> 00:26:09,067
You're texting Dad?

401
00:26:14,433 --> 00:26:16,200
This is just
the initial presentation.

402
00:26:16,333 --> 00:26:18,667
I didn't expect
that they would send you.

403
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:20,533
Why did you have to lie?

404
00:26:20,667 --> 00:26:23,233
Mr. Fuentes didn't request
that I do the presentation.

405
00:26:23,367 --> 00:26:26,833
The Paradiso Escano deal needs
the best person for the job.

406
00:26:26,967 --> 00:26:28,300
And that's Paolo, and not you.

407
00:26:28,433 --> 00:26:29,167
Thanks, Dad.

408
00:26:29,300 --> 00:26:32,500
That's my chance
to impress Marj.

409
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:36,400
Don't be nervous. We got this.

410
00:26:36,533 --> 00:26:38,767
You got this.
You're Miss Tough Girl, right?

411
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:42,500
Does that mean Premium Homes
Realty is here, too?

412
00:26:42,667 --> 00:26:44,133
Love.

413
00:26:44,267 --> 00:26:47,333
Randall, I'm here to work.
Please don't bother me.

414
00:26:47,467 --> 00:26:49,767
And we have nothing
left to talk about.

415
00:26:49,900 --> 00:26:51,767
Leave me alone.
